      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COURSE OF ACTION (1) settled back in a small field then went through the gears nicely to get up for second on debut over 1400m at Scone last start. Coming back in trip is the slight query but with a good tempo up front he will be tough to hold out. FINED FOR SPEEDING (5) over-raced and was never a factor when resuming over 1200m at Scone, although his best work did come late. Should settle better with that run under the belt and with 2kgs less under today's scale is open to sharp improvement. ARTIE'S MAGIC (2) raced on the speed but couldn't accelerate in heavy going at the end of 1412m at Coffs Harbour last time. Far better placed back to this trip on firmer ground. Should be there at the business end. MONUMENTAL (3) started at $2.30 on debut last start at Scone but was under the pump from the outset after beginning slowly. Back in trip but the blinkers go on - a form reversal will not surprise. WHITTELLO SUN (4) impressed first-up over 1000m and this trip is more suitable.",
